# BPWCISLO.com — Site Rules & PRD

## Owner
Brian Patrick Wcislo — strategist, designer, product builder. 25+ years in digital. Based in Costa Rica.

## Purpose
Personal portfolio site selling operational leverage and custom app development to operations-heavy businesses ($5M–$250M).

## Design Language
Apple-inspired minimalism. Clean, spacious, confident. Every element earns its place.

- **Inspiration**: Apple Mac mini product page (scroll-driven reveals, large imagery, centered typography, alternating light/dark sections)
- **Tone**: Professional but human. Direct. No fluff.

## Color Palette (CSS Variables)

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `--accent` | `#65a30d` | Primary green — CTAs, highlights, active states |
| `--accent-hover` | `#4d7c0f` | Hover state for accent |
| `--slate-900` | `#0f172a` | Dark backgrounds, primary text |
| `--slate-50` | `#f8fafc` | Light section backgrounds |
| `--white` | `#ffffff` | Card backgrounds, body |
| `--gold` | `#d97706` | Geometric accent shape only |

## Typography

- **Display**: `Sora` (headings, cards) — 400/500/600/700 weights
- **Body**: `Inter` (paragraphs, UI) — 400/500/600 weights
- **h1**: `clamp(2.75rem, 6vw, 4rem)` weight 400, bold via `<strong>`
- **h2**: `clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 3.25rem)` weight 700
- **Body**: 1rem / 1.6 line-height

## Spacing Scale

`--space-1` (4px) through `--space-24` (96px). Use variables, never raw pixels for layout spacing.

## Page Sections (top to bottom)

1. **Hero** — Headline with blur-reveal animation, tagline with green underline on "boring businesses", speech-bubble CTA
2. **What I Do** — Rotating word headline, 3 service cards with animated SVG icons (scissors, building blocks, rocket)
3. **Selected Work** — Full-width project galleries (Apple-style horizontal scroll, snap, dots, arrows, click-to-navigate)
4. **Who I Work With** — Testimonial cards (2-col grid, italic quotes, green titles, 3D tilt on hover)
5. **Trusted Collaborators** — Partner logos with category labels
6. **About Brian** — Bio + photo grid, Essentials horizontal card carousel
7. **Contact** — Form with floating labels, green checkmarks, speech-bubble submit button

## Interactive Features

| Feature | Scope | Trigger |
|---------|-------|---------|
| Scroll progress bar | Global | Scroll position |
| Blur-reveal text | Section headings | IntersectionObserver |
| Stat counters | "25+", "10", "102x" | IntersectionObserver |
| Speech bubble morph | Hero CTA, Contact submit | Load sequence / scroll |
| Green underline wipe | "boring businesses", section outro | Load sequence / scroll position |
| Cursor spotlight | Dark project cards, Partners | mousemove |
| 3D tilt | Testimonial cards | mousemove |
| Magnetic buttons | Hero CTA only | mousemove (disabled past 50% scroll) |
| Gallery dot indicators | Project galleries | scroll sync |
| Rotating words | Services headline | setInterval |
| Service icon animations | Scissors, blocks, rocket | hover |
| Floating shapes | Background circles/squares | mousemove + requestAnimationFrame |
| Section zoom reveal | All reveal targets | IntersectionObserver (scale 0.97→1) |
| Form validation | Contact form | input/blur/submit |

## Animation Principles

- Use `cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)` for reveals and morphs
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` — all JS animations check this
- Stagger grid children at 0.12s intervals
- Hero entrance sequence: headline letters → tagline → button → underline → bubble morph
- Keep transitions under 1s for interactions, up to 1.2s for reveals

## Project Galleries

- Horizontal scroll with `scroll-snap-type: x mandatory`
- Slides: `92vw` mobile, `min(72vw, 960px)` desktop
- Center-snap with peek of adjacent slides
- Nav arrows + dot indicators + click-to-navigate on partial slides
- Placeholder slides use gradient backgrounds (`placeholder-cool`, `placeholder-warm`, `placeholder-sage`)
- Dark cards get inverted placeholder/dot/arrow colors

## Contact Form

- Fields: Name (required), Company, Email (required), Phone, Challenge textarea
- Name + Company on row 1, Email + Phone on row 2, textarea below
- Floating labels (lift + turn green on focus)
- Green checkmark SVG on valid fields
- Shake animation on invalid submit
- Submits via mailto:brian@bpwcislo.com (compose in mail client)

## Responsive Breakpoints

| Breakpoint | Behavior |
|-----------|----------|
| < 480px | Shapes hidden, form rows stack, smallest text sizes |
| < 640px | Nav links shrink + scroll, partner grid stacks |
| < 768px | Hero stacks (text below photo centered), single-column layouts |
| ≥ 768px | Hero side-by-side, desktop gallery sizes, full nav |

## File Structure

Single-file architecture: all CSS, HTML, and JS in `index.html`. No external stylesheets or script files. Images alongside in project root.

## Coding Conventions

- CSS custom properties for all colors, spacing, and fonts
- No CSS frameworks — vanilla CSS with modern features (grid, clamp, scroll-snap)
- Vanilla JS — no libraries or frameworks
- IntersectionObserver for scroll-triggered effects
- `passive: true` on all scroll listeners
- Semantic HTML with accessible labels on interactive elements
